Onderzoekers van #TilburgU zijn op zoek naar ouders met kinderen tussen de 1 en 10 jaar die interesse hebben om al hun ervaringen, zowel positieve als negatieve, rondom opvoeden tijdens de COVID-19 uitbraak met ons te delen. Wil je meedoen?

We perform especially well on SDG 16 related research and university governance measures. https://www.tilburguniversity.edu/current/news/more-news/tilburg-university-ranks-high-peace-justice-and-strong-institutions

Pleased to report that I am winning my family's quarantine beard competition. My first beard since 1987.
That same daughter, Robin Perry, is the editor for my upcoming book. A wonderful editor, although I may be biased.
Gardening season starts much earlier here than in Butler!
Peas and lettuce growing strong, should be transplanting the tomato, cucumber, and squash seedlings outside later this week.

And if you are eager to get a jump on your summer reading, you may pre-order the new book I have co-authored with @TomCollina, "The Button: The New Nuclear Arms Race and Presidential Power from Truman to Trump," here:
If you are a fellow Opera fan, I can highly recommend @MetOpera on Demand, although at my current pace I fear I will have watched every video before the year is out.
In these unusual times I have taken some time away from social media and instead busied myself with my upcoming book, my garden, and a steady diet of opera to keep up the spirits.
And debuting my quarantine beard
